      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-World Use Case: E-Learning Platforms"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In e-learning, personalized voices enhance engagement by providing consistent narration across courses. For instance, a platform using Qwen3 TTS CustomVoice can clone an instructor's voice from a short recording, then generate lesson audio on-demand. This reduces production time from days to minutes, with latency low enough to support real-time quiz feedback. Integration with learning management systems (LMS) is straightforward via webhooks, where audio files are stored in cloud storage like AWS S3 and referenced in course modules."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance testing in this context shows that a 100-word script synthesizes in under 300ms, enabling seamless playback without buffering. Cost-wise, at $0.004 per 1000 characters, generating 10 hours of audio (approximately 90,000 words) costs around $3.60, making it viable for large-scale deployments. Teams should monitor usage with the API's built-in analytics dashboard to track character consumption and optimize text preprocessing."
          }
        ]
      },
